{"id": "EUVD-2022-54894", "enisaUuid": "dad138b0-2f7e-36fc-b5ec-2d2627a45cee", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm/huge_memory: Fix xarray node memory leak\n\nIf xas_split_alloc() fails to allocate the necessary nodes to complete the\nxarray entry split, it sets the xa_state to -ENOMEM, which xas_nomem()\nthen interprets as \"Please allocate more memory\", not as \"Please free\nany unnecessary memory\" (which was the intended outcome).  It's confusing\nto use xas_nomem() to free memory in this context, so call xas_destroy()\ninstead.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:10:52", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:46:55", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c0c84962e297927ba57fd6ddc2bb000c9d149655", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/95c8181b4947e000f3b9b8e5918d899fce77b93d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/69a37a8ba1b408a1c7616494aa7018e4b3844cbe"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49334"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0907cd86-9526-3fd4-a42d-81827d6f5354", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6b24ca4a1a8d4ee3221d6d44ddbb99f542e4bda3 <c0c84962e297927ba57fd6ddc2bb000c9d149655"}, {"id": "1d9a607a-2ec5-3e25-af9e-1222df5a458b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "3a70859d-a7d0-3155-9ab9-4ec3b12f1bda", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.15"}, {"id": "45792645-3798-3021-8d45-e2603fc5402d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "46bde44c-9a98-318e-a47d-796076353cad", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.4"}, {"id": "857bc3b9-928f-3880-bc62-3f4496c34a6d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6b24ca4a1a8d4ee3221d6d44ddbb99f542e4bda3 <69a37a8ba1b408a1c7616494aa7018e4b3844cbe"}, {"id": "88de6096-b667-3109-9606-9eaf8a3c3660", "product": {"name": "Linux